= Review funding for the Buran space shuttle program

For more than a decade, the Soviet Union has been working towards developing a capable space shuttle that rivals those seen in the United States. Although it puts a heavy strain on the Soviet budget, it is broadly supported amongst the politburo and cushions the Soviet economy with a million jobs. 

Shall we continue funding the program, or redirect funds into other areas of our economy?

